msgid "# Contributing"
msgstr "# 贡献指南"

msgid "## Building and Testing"
msgstr "## 构建与测试"

msgid ""
"It's recommended to set up a local development environment to build vllm-ascend and run tests\n"
"before you submit a PR."
msgstr "建议在提交 PR 之前，先搭建本地开发环境来构建 vllm-ascend 并运行测试。"

msgid "### Set up a development environment"
msgstr "### 搭建开发环境"

msgid ""
"Theoretically, the vllm-ascend build is only supported on Linux because\n"
"`vllm-ascend` dependency `torch_npu` only supports Linux."
msgstr "理论上，vllm-ascend 的构建仅支持 Linux 系统，因为其依赖 `torch_npu` 仅支持 Linux。"

msgid ""
"But you can still set up a development environment on Linux/Windows/macOS for linting and running basic\n"
"tests."
msgstr "但你仍然可以在 Linux/Windows/macOS 上搭建开发环境，用于代码检查及运行基础测试。"

msgid "#### Run lint locally"
msgstr "#### 本地运行代码检查"

msgid "#### Run CI locally"
msgstr "#### 本地运行 CI"

msgid ""
"After completing \"Run lint\" setup, you can run CI (Continuous integration)"
" locally:"
msgstr "完成“运行代码检查”设置后，你可以在本地运行 CI（持续集成）："

msgid "#### Submit the commit"
msgstr "#### 提交代码"

msgid ""
"🎉 Congratulations! You have completed the development environment setup."
msgstr "🎉 恭喜！你已完成开发环境搭建。"

msgid "### Testing locally"
msgstr "### 本地测试"

msgid ""
"You can refer to [Testing](./testing.md)  to set up a testing environment "
"and running tests locally."
msgstr "你可以参考[测试指南](./testing.md)来搭建测试环境并在本地运行测试。"

msgid "## DCO and Signed-off-by"
msgstr "## DCO 与 Signed-off-by"

msgid ""
"When contributing changes to this project, you must agree to the DCO. "
"Commits must include a `Signed-off-by:` header which certifies agreement "
"with the terms of the DCO (Developer Certificate of Origin)."
msgstr ""
"向本项目贡献代码时，你必须同意 DCO。提交记录必须包含 `Signed-off-by:` 头部，以证明你同意 DCO（开发者原创证书）的条款。"

msgid "Using `-s` with `git commit` will automatically add this header."
msgstr "使用 `git commit -s` 命令将自动添加此头部信息。"

msgid "## PR Title and Classification"
msgstr "## PR 标题与分类"

msgid ""
"Only specific types of PRs will be reviewed. The PR title is prefixed "
"appropriately to indicate the type of change. Please use one of the "
"following:"
msgstr "仅特定类型的 PR 会被审查。PR 标题需添加适当前缀以指明变更类型。请使用以下前缀之一："

msgid ""
"- `[Attention]` for new features or optimization in attention.\n"
"- `[Communicator]` for new features or optimization in communicators.\n"
"- `[ModelRunner]` for new features or optimization in model runner.\n"
"- `[Platform]` for new features or optimization in platform.\n"
"- `[Worker]` for new features or optimization in worker.\n"
"- `[Core]` for new features or optimization  in the core vllm-ascend logic (such as platform, attention, communicators, model runner)\n"
"- `[Kernel]` for changes affecting compute kernels and ops.\n"
"- `[BugFix]` for bug fixes.\n"
"- `[Doc]` for documentation fixes and improvements.\n"
"- `[Test]` for tests (such as unit tests).\n"
"- `[CI]` for build or continuous integration improvements.\n"
"- `[Misc]` for PRs that do not fit the above categories. Please use this sparingly."
msgstr ""
"- `[Attention]` 用于注意力机制的新功能或优化。\n"
"- `[Communicator]` 用于通信器的新功能或优化。\n"
"- `[ModelRunner]` 用于模型运行器的新功能或优化。\n"
"- `[Platform]` 用于平台的新功能或优化。\n"
"- `[Worker]` 用于工作节点的新功能或优化。\n"
"- `[Core]` 用于 vllm-ascend 核心逻辑（如平台、注意力机制、通信器、模型运行器）的新功能或优化。\n"
"- `[Kernel]` 用于影响计算内核和算子的变更。\n"
"- `[BugFix]` 用于错误修复。\n"
"- `[Doc]` 用于文档修复和改进。\n"
"- `[Test]` 用于测试（如单元测试）。\n"
"- `[CI]` 用于构建或持续集成的改进。\n"
"- `[Misc]` 用于不属于上述类别的 PR，请谨慎使用。"

msgid ""
"If the PR spans more than one category, please include all relevant "
"prefixes."
msgstr "如果 PR 涉及多个类别，请包含所有相关前缀。"

msgid "## Others"
msgstr "## 其他"

msgid ""
"You may find more information about contributing to vLLM Ascend backend plugin on [<u>docs.vllm.ai</u>](https://docs.vllm.ai/en/latest/contributing).\n"
"If you encounter any problems while contributing, feel free to submit a PR to improve the documentation to help other developers."
msgstr ""
"你可以在 [<u>docs.vllm.ai</u>](https://docs.vllm.ai/en/latest/contributing) 上找到更多关于向 vLLM Ascend 后端插件贡献的信息。\n"
"如果在贡献过程中遇到任何问题，欢迎提交 PR 改进文档，以帮助其他开发者。"
